            <abstract>
    <p>In Ethiopian tradition there are four homilies on the Annunciation attributed to John Chrysostom. They are labelled by Proverbio
    as <ref type="work" corresp="LIT6721ChrAnnun">Eth A</ref>, Eth B (the present record), <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2107OntheA">Eth C</ref> and
    <ref type="work" corresp="LIT6713DerYaq">Eth D</ref>. They usually appear together e. g. in <ref type="mss" corresp="BerOrFol117"/>, <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML3442"/>.
  Eth D is attributed in the manuscripts to Jacob of Sarugh.</p>
